Set up your organization to use the Service Analytics by enabling CRM Analytics and creating and assigning permission sets.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To set up CRM Analytics users:	Manage CRM Analytics

Each Service Analytics license is a single-user license that provides access to Service Analytics. It includes a single Service Analytics app single-user license. The table shows data storage limits for the app.

Service Analytics Data Storage Limits
LICENSE	LIMIT
Analytics Cloud - Service Analytics	25 million rows when used without CRM Analytics Growth license.
Analytics Cloud - Additional Data Rows	100 million rows.

To give administrators or users in your org access to the Service Analytics, enable CRM Analytics and assign ready-made permission sets to them. By assigning permission sets, you also assign the Service Analytics permission set license.

First, enable Analytics. In Salesforce Setup, enter Analytics in the QuickFind field, then click Getting Started.
Click Enable Analytics.
Now, assign permission sets. In Salesforce Setup, enter Users in the QuickFind field.
Click Permission Sets.
Scroll through the list of permission sets until you see Service Analytics Admin and Service Analytics User.

To assign user-level access to Service Analytics, assign the Service Analytics User permission set.
Click Service Analytics User.
Click Manage Assignments, then Add Assignments.
Check the boxes next to the names of the users who require access to the app.
Click Assign, then click Done.

After you’ve completed these steps, create and share Service Analytics with the users in your organization. Users can only explore Service Analytics dashboards and datasets after you’ve shared the app with them.
title: Setting Up Service Analytics
